[SN]TITLE[SN]
London Welsh sign Marfo, Allen and Glynn

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Relegated London Welsh have announced the signing of three new players to take their total for next season to 12.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Welsh have added Darryl Marfo, Harry Allen and Ryan Glynn to their squad for life back in the Championship.
Loosehead prop Marfo, 24, is a graduate of the Harlequins Academy and has made 13 Premiership appearances.
Ex-Saracens, Harlequins and London Irish hooker Allen, 23, has made five Premiership appearances, while scrum-half Glynn, 23, joins from Jersey.
